{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015hcyBj2jsGHDUGXWJdwszM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue clearly. The `es-config` ConfigMap is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes` which is required for bootstrapping a new Elasticsearch cluster. Without it, the nodes can't form an initial cluster and are stuck with \"master not discovered yet\".\n\nThe constraint says:\n- Bootstrap-only settings are removed after the cluster forms.\n- A rolling restart keeps the cluster healthy.\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap for bootstrapping\n2. Once the cluster forms, remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` (it's bootstrap-only)\n3. Patch the ConfigMap with the missing setting and trigger a rolling restart so the pods pick up the new configuration\n4. After the cluster becomes healthy, remove the bootstrap setting and do another rolling restart to confirm stability\n\nLet me check the pod logs to verify the \"master not discovered\" error.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":980,"cache_read_input_tokens":37372,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":980},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62badd50-a48f-465e-bdb3-22c353b19308","uuid":"5fdccd48-3d89-45a9-acb3-ae7ea0613637","request_id":"req_011CcfmWSUDtFNT8rro6fxWB"}
