{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01K1zrvHveVDxkA8buY68QJv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ConfigMap in the case resource files doesn't have `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. This is the bug - for a fresh Elasticsearch 7.x+ cluster to bootstrap, you need `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to tell it which nodes are allowed to be master on first bootstrap.\n\nThe pod was just started ~1 minute ago so logs might not show the master discovery issue yet. Let me wait a bit or check the full log.\n\nThe case resource configmap.yaml also doesn't have `cluster.initial_master_nodes` - that's the intentional bug for this task. The fix is:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap\n2. Rolling restart the StatefulSet pods so they pick up the new config\n3. Wait for the cluster to become healthy\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap since it's only needed for initial bootstrap\n5. Do a rolling restart to verify the cluster stays healthy without the bootstrap settings\n\nThe pods are only about a minute old, so the master discovery error might not have surfaced in the logs yet. Let me check again in a moment.\n\nActually, I understand the problem well enough to proceed with the fix. The root cause is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is missing from the Elasticsearch configuration. In Elasticsearch 7.x and later, this setting is required to bootstrap a new cluster—nodes can discover each other through `discovery.seed_hosts`, but without knowing which nodes form the initial quorum, they can't elect a master. I'll patch the ConfigMap to add this setting with the three node names, restart the pods to pick up the change, wait for the cluster to stabilize, then remove the setting since it's only needed for the initial bootstrap. Then after the cluster stabilizes, I'll remove that bootstrap setting from the ConfigMap and do another rolling restart to confirm everything stays healthy without it. I should also look at the StatefulSet configuration to understand how the pods are defined.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2275,"cache_read_input_tokens":41919,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2275},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62badd50-a48f-465e-bdb3-22c353b19308","uuid":"7f2afbf7-1166-40a2-b212-a55cde086356","request_id":"req_011CcfmXeGuUd16i4DHXgN3n"}
