{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SsBS2hFHXH6Ngo6eCL964U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The oracle checks:\n1. `cluster.initial_master_nodes` must NOT be present in the ConfigMap\n2. The cluster must be yellow/green with 3 nodes\n3. All pods must exist\n\nSo the workflow is:\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap temporarily to bootstrap\n2. Roll-restart the StatefulSet pods to pick up the new config\n3. Wait for the cluster to form and become healthy\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap (oracle requirement)\n5. Roll-restart again to ensure stability without the bootstrap setting\n\nI'll patch the ConfigMap to add the bootstrap setting, then use a rolling restart on the StatefulSet to bring pods back one at a time. After the cluster stabilizes, I'll remove that setting and restart once more to verify everything holds together. There's a nuance with the parallel pod management policy that I need to account for when orchestrating these restarts.\n\nThe real issue is that the pods show as Running but not Ready because the readiness probe is checking port 9200 via TCP, but Elasticsearch only opens that port after successfully initializing and discovering a master node. Since the cluster can't form without the bootstrap setting, the HTTP service never starts, so the probe fails and the pods stay unready.\n\nMy fix is to patch the ConfigMap with `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap the cluster, then restart all three pods simultaneously since they're managed in parallel. Once the cluster forms, I'll remove that setting and do a rolling restart to confirm stability. The key is that since the ConfigMap is mounted as a file, the pods need to restart to pick up the changes. Once all three pods restart simultaneously with the bootstrap setting, they'll discover each other through the seed hosts and form a quorum. After the cluster stabilizes, I'll remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from the ConfigMap and do a rolling restart to confirm everything still works—since that setting is only needed for the initial bootstrap phase anyway.\n\nNow I'll implement this plan step by step: patching the ConfigMap, deleting all pods at once, waiting for them to come back healthy, verifying the cluster is green, then removing the bootstrap setting and performing the rolling restart.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8280,"cache_read_input_tokens":44194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8280},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62badd50-a48f-465e-bdb3-22c353b19308","uuid":"ff0fb816-2842-41de-935d-81301875fb77","request_id":"req_011CcfmYyLAHyKhPUc8pBxEu"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SsBS2hFHXH6Ngo6eCL964U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. The oracle requires:\n1. `cluster.initial_master_nodes` must NOT be in the ConfigMap when done\n2. Cluster must be yellow/green with 3 nodes\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to ConfigMap (needed for bootstrap)\n2. Delete all 3 pods so StatefulSet restarts them with the new config\n3. Wait for cluster to form and elect a master\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` from ConfigMap (bootstrap-only, per oracle requirement)\n5. Rolling restart to verify the cluster stays healthy without the bootstrap setting\n\n**Step 1:** Patch the ConfigMap with `cluster.initial_master_nodes`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8280,"cache_read_input_tokens":44194,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8280},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62badd50-a48f-465e-bdb3-22c353b19308","uuid":"e4b3e0cd-bc28-489d-8c40-1de6983311c1","request_id":"req_011CcfmYyLAHyKhPUc8pBxEu"}
