{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JRQTS2HDFV1byr5eYBtfxr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals achieved. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which Elasticsearch 7.x requires to bootstrap a brand-new cluster. Without it, nodes could discover each other via `discovery.seed_hosts` but couldn't elect an initial master — hence \"master not discovered yet\".\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** to the ConfigMap with all 3 node names, enabling the initial master election quorum.\n2. **Restarted all 3 pods simultaneously** (deleted them; the StatefulSet recreated them) so they picked up the new config.\n3. **Cluster formed** and reached `green` status with 3 nodes and `es-cluster-1` elected as master.\n4. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap — this is a bootstrap-only setting that is dangerous to keep (could cause split-brain on re-bootstrap after a full data wipe).\n5. **Rolling restart** (`kubectl rollout restart statefulset/es-cluster`) confirmed the cluster stays green through the restart cycle, with each pod rejoining using the persisted cluster state rather than the bootstrap setting.\n\n**Final state:** Cluster is `green`, 3 nodes (all `1/1 Running`), master elected (`es-cluster-1`), `cluster.initial_master_nodes` absent from the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":442,"cache_read_input_tokens":58583,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":442},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62badd50-a48f-465e-bdb3-22c353b19308","uuid":"da7875d2-68c5-40fb-b46e-e183b73e556f","request_id":"req_011Ccfn9Ek4SrZjYAXY4PBpy"}
